interrogation1:
Late at night, Eleven returns to the Eastside TV Station on Fifth Avenue. She receives a phone call from herself, asking if she is there to destroy the phantom that caused the Ghost Call incidents. Eleven confirms that she is and that she wants to erase all memory of her show. The phantom tells her that as long as they both exist, there will always be another call at 3AM and that the world will always be full of things that Eleven would rather not hear. The line goes dead and Eleven begins to hallucinate a scene on the building's rooftop and the voices of her producers instructing her to pander harder to her audience.

At the MBCC, The Chief receives an alert of a Mania spike in Eastside. As they arrive at the TV Station, the phones of everybody in the street begin to ring. Eleven's voice says that she wants to resume her show and tells the Chief to come to the roof, where they find Eleven unconscious in a swirling mass of a Mania energy, holding an antique terminal with an active phone call. While the voice continues to talk through the call, the Chief Shackles Eleven. They are overcome by a wave of grief, but Eleven is shocked awake and uses her ability to destroy the terminal in her hand. She turns to the Chief and says that she has taken care of things now, and asks to be taken into custody. As they leave the station, a bulletin announces that Call at 3AM has been put on indefinite hiatus.

//You met Eleven again at the TV station, where she as threatened by a power similar to hers. After resolving this threat, Eleven voluntarily returned to the Bureau with you for detention and interrogation.//

